The unmanned cargo ship carries 7,900 pounds of supplies including food, water, clothes for the astronauts, as well as material to support science and research probes

3D printer sent to space An unmanned cargo ship blasted off late on Tuesday to the International Space Station carrying scientific equipment, including a 3D printer, and provisions for astronauts. Today's Paper More In: NATIONAL Tweet
title: Cygnus blasts off to ISS
